The paper proposes a novel tensor graph convolutional neural network for conducting convolution on factorizable graphs, with a focus on sequential dynamic graphs and cross-attribute graphs. This work involves graph convolution, graph pooling, and matrix completion, which are all related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also involves neural networks and optimization, which are related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
